<br>
The exception would be of course for expansions. Obviously marketing wants hard release dates. But smart companies lead marketing campaigns with &quot;summer of...&quot; or spring of...&quot; and NOT anything specific until the project manager is confident the expansion will be ready. <p>Kzan Verto<BR>
